==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*kiolo-'', from Indo-European ''*gawl-'' ‘ball, swelling’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[kiol]] (Dutch [[kiel]]), Old High German [[kiol]] (German [[Kiel]]), Old Norse [[kjóll]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ʧe:ol/}}

===Noun===
{{Unicode|'''ċēol'''}} ''m'' (plural {{Unicode|'''[[ceolas|ċēolas]]'''}})
# the [[keel]] of a ship
# a [[ship]]
#:''Ceol on lande stod'': the ship stood on the land.  (''Beowulf'')

